    <statement><p>Solve the equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ {4\mathopen{}\left(p+8\right)-10\mathopen{}\left(p-2\right)}={52}  }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="31" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\{0\}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
4(p +8) -10(p-2)       \amp = 52 \\
4(p +8) +(-10)(p+(-2)) \amp = 52 \\
4p +4 \cdot 8 +(-10) \cdot p +(-10) \cdot (-2) \amp = 52 \\
4p +32 -10p +20 \amp = 52 \\
4p -10p +32+20 \amp = 52 \\
      -6p +52 \amp = 52 \\
      -6p +52\mathbf{{}-52} \amp = 52\mathbf{{}-52} \\
      -6p             \amp = 0 \\
      \frac{-6p}{-6} \amp = \frac{0}{-6} \\
      p                      \amp = 0
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The solution to this equation is <m>0</m>. To stress that this is a value assigned to <m>p</m>, some report <m>p = 0</m>. We can also say that the solution set is <m>\{0\}</m>, or that <m>p\in\left\{0\right\}</m>. If we substitute <m>0</m> in for <m>p</m> in the original equation <m>4\mathopen{}\left(p+8\right)-10\mathopen{}\left(p-2\right)=52</m>, the equation will be true. Please check this on your own; it is an important habit.</p>
</solution>
